The paper deals with quantum algorithms and their complexities for Boolean functions, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of quantum mechanics in the algorithms suggests that it also belongs to the sub-category of quantum information (cs.QI). The paper also discusses communication complexity, which falls under the sub-category of distributed systems (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents results on the gap between quantum and classical complexities, which is relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
